definition.value: Is a quantification of some aspect of the optic disk
optic nerve head measurement
Is a quantification of the area of the optic disc
Is a quantification of the rim of the optic disc
Is a quantification of the ratio between optic cup and optic disc, used in the diagnosis of glaucoma
Is a quantification of the area of the optic cup
quantification of the force applied by the hand to pull on or suspend from objects
quantification of some aspect of facial pigmentation, such as the number, size or location of pigmentation spots
quantification of any change in an indiviual's blood pressure, for example in response to treatment with a antihypertensive agent
quantification of any change in an indiviual's systolic blood pressure
quantification of any change in an indiviual's diastolic blood pressure
quantification of some aspect of behavioural disinhibition, including risky and impulsive behaviours. Behavioural disinhibition can be a marker for certain kinds of mental or behavioural disorders.
quantification of an individual's appreciation of red wine
quantification of an individual's appreciation of white wine
quantification of an individual's appreciation of wine
quantification of some aspect of cytotoxity such as survival time or cell viability
A reported family history of lung cancer in one or more family members.
quantification of the activity of the von Willebrand factor-cleaving protease ADAMTS13
quantification of the difference in intraocular pressure between two time points
quantification of the unknown substance X12063 in blood
quantification of mannose in a sample
quantification of the amount of DNA methylation in a target gene
quantification of the agressiveness of a (usually malignant) cancer

Quantification of the cytoarchitecture of a prostate cancer sample, used in the evaluation of cancer prognosis. Cancers with a higher Gleason score are generally more aggressive and have a worse prognosis.
Quantification of dehydroepiandrosterone sulfate (DHEA-S) in a sample. DHEA-S is a metabolite of dehydroepiandrosterone (DHEA), the most abundant circulating steroid hormone in humans.

Quantification of luteinizing hormone (LH) in a sample. In females, an acute rise of LH ("LH surge") triggers ovulation and development of the corpus luteum. In males, where LH had also been called interstitial cellâ€“stimulating hormone (ICSH), it stimulates Leydig cell production of testosterone. It acts synergistically with FSH.
quantification of prolactin in a sample
quantification of progesterone in a sample
Quantification of abnormal androgen status in humans, calculated as the ratio of the total level of testosterone divided by the SHBG level, multiplied by a constant (usually 100)
quantification of the existence and severity of depressive symptoms, usually via a questionnaire such as the Center for Epidemiological Studies Depression Scale (CES-D)

Quantification of the amount of ticagrelor in a sample. Ticagrelor is a platelet aggregation inhibitor used for the prevention of thrombotic events in people with acute coronary syndrome or myocardial infarction with ST elevation.

quantification of some aspect of an allergy, for example whether an allergy is present or its severity. Allergies are commonly quantified through measurement of allergen-specific IgE in the blood or skin reaction after puncture of skin through a droplet of allergen extract (skin prick test)
quantification of some aspect of skin pigmentation, such as saturation, darkness or skin sensitivity to sun
quantification of some aspect of drug use, such as whether drug use occured, over what period of time it occured and what dosage was used
quantification of some aspect of SSRI use
quantification of some aspect of NSAID use
quantification of some aspect of aspirin use
quantification in a urine sample of 3-hydroxypropylmercapturic acid, one of the main metabolites of acrolein, an important constituent of cigarette smoke with well documented toxic effects

quantification in a urine sample of 3-hydroxy-1-methylpropylmercapturic acid, one of the main metabolites of crotonaldehyde, an important constituent of cigarette smoke with well documented toxic effects
quantification of the presence or severity of an allergy to some food
quantification of the presence or severity of an allergy to peanuts
quantification of the presence or severity of an allergy to eggs
quantification of the presence or severity of an allergy to milk or other dairy products
Quantification of the amount of AR-C124910XX in a sample. AR-C124910XX is the active metabolite of ticagrelor formed by O-deethylation.
quantification of the amount and location of Lewy bodies in a brain biopsy sample
a seropositivity measurement is the quantification of an individual's exposure to a certain pathogen through the presence or absence in blood of pathogen specific circulating antibodies
Chlamydia pneumoniae seropositivity is the result of a measurement of circulating C. pneumoniae specific antibodies
herpes virus seropositivity is the result of a measurement of circulating herpes virus specific antibodies
cytomegalovirus seropositivity is the result of a measurement of circulating cytomegalovirus specific antibodies
Influenza A seropositivity is the result of a measurement of circulating Influenza A specific antibodies
human herpesvirus 8 seropositivity is the result of a measurement of circulating human herpesvirus 8 specific antibodies
